{
  "texts": [
    "[68,285], the effect of uniaxial strain on the unstrained graphene lattice vectors r and RLVs g is expressed through layer-dependent transformation matrices M l r l = M T l r, g l = M -1 l g M l ≃ 1 + E T where R(θ) is a rotation matrix.",
    "Heterostrain constrains the parameters to satisfy θ 1 = -θ 2 = θ/2, φ 1 = φ 2 = φ, and ϵ 1 = -ϵ 2 = ϵ/2.",
    "To first order in ϵ and θ, the twist angle is unaffected.",
    "In analogy with the unstrained case, the new basis moiré RLVs are, in terms of the basis monolayer RLVs,b 1 = (M -1 1 -M -1 2)(b G2 -b G1), b 2 = (M -1 1 -M -1 2)b G1.",
    "(137)This will affect the sampling of the momentum grid.The strained and rotated intralayer kinetic term in valley τ becomes ⟨p, l| H BM |p ′, l⟩ = ℏv F [M l (pτ A l) -K τ] • τ σ x -σ y δ p,p ′ (138) A = β 2a (ϵ xxϵ yy, -2ϵ xy)where β = 3.14, and a CC is the C-C bond length."
  ]
